GW2 Unit Frames is a closed-source project. This repository publishes only the
addon's documentation and screenshots. The source code is intentionally not
made public.


Why this project is closed source
---------------------------------
The addon reads Guild Wars 2 client memory to display live buffs, vitals, and
related party/squad information. Keeping the implementation private avoids
publishing a ready-made template for misuse, while still shipping a normal
informational overlay for players.


Permitted use
-------------
You may download and use GW2 Unit Frames free of charge, including while
streaming, recording, or making videos or other content — on monetised
channels as well as personal ones. Streamers and content creators are welcome
to feature and showcase the addon. You may also quote or reuse this
repository's documentation and screenshots when describing, reviewing, or
showcasing GW2 Unit Frames, with attribution.

This permission does not let you sell GW2 Unit Frames, charge others for
access to it, or bundle it into a paid product or service — see Restrictions
below.


Distribution
------------
Official builds are published free of charge on GitHub Releases:
https://github.com/michael-stubbs/GW2-UnitFrames/releases

You may redistribute an official release binary unchanged and free of charge,
provided you point users to the official Releases page for updates. This
conveys no right to modify, sell, or reverse engineer the software.


Restrictions
------------
Except as expressly permitted above, you may not copy, modify, redistribute,
sell, decompile, disassemble, or otherwise reverse engineer the GW2 Unit
Frames software or attempt to recover its source code, without prior written
permission from the author.


ArenaNet developer access
-------------------------
The author welcomes scrutiny from the people who make Guild Wars 2. Verified
ArenaNet employees may request read-only access to the complete source code in
order to review the addon's behaviour and confirm its compliance with the
Guild Wars 2 User Agreement and rules of conduct. To request access, open an
issue on this repository or contact the author via the Discord link on the
project page.

Such access is granted for review purposes only and conveys no license to use,
copy, modify, or redistribute the source code.


